text: Canton of Marseille-Les Olives is a former canton located within the commune of Marseille in the Bouches-du-Rhône department of France. It was created 27 February 2003 by the decree 2003-156 of that date. It was disbanded following the French canton reorganisation which came into effect in March 2015. Its population was 34,060 in 2012.Populations légales 2012: Téléchargement du fichier d'ensemble, INSEE Elected to represent the canton in the General Council of Bouches-du-Rhône : * Marius Masse (PS, 2001-2008) ==Area== It is composed of the part of the 13th arrondissement of Marseille not within the cantons of Marseille - Saint-Just and Marseille-La Rose. == See also == * Arrondissement of Marseille * Cantons of the Bouches-du-Rhône department * Communes of the Bouches-du-Rhône department ==References== Category:Former cantons of Marseille Marseille-Les Olives Category:2015 disestablishments in France Category:States and territories disestablished in 2015 Category:2003 establishments in France
